===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[young]] [[male]] person, usually a [[child]] or [[teenager]].
#:''the '''boys''' were playing kickball in the mud.''
# {{US}} {{context|racist|offensive|archaic|pejorative}} A male [[African-American]] of any age.
# {{rfv-sense}} A male servant. (Compare French [[garçon]].)
# {{context|colloquial|always used in plural}} Male (usually adult) friends.
#: ''I’m going out for a few drinks with the '''boys'''.''
# A man of any age, used as a friendly diminutive, or of a man who is merely younger than the speaker.
#: ''Whatever else you say about him, the '''boy''' can play.''
#: 1977: ''I like the boy.'' &mdash; Australian entertainer [[w:Bert Newton|Bert Newton]], to [[w:Mohammed Ali|Mohammed Ali]] at the 1977 Logie Awards, famously unaware of how insulting this is under the US usage above [http://www.abc.net.au/thingo/txt/s1088100.htm]
# An [[adult]] male, particularly when used by straight women or gay men to refer to someone considered attractive.
# {{context|figurative|endearing}} A proud parent's son (of any age.)

